01KS4PQN845J3WNVJV73HJ0ZB6.message:
## Lesson: UnsupportedOperationError should be caught silently, not logged repeatedly
Generic catch-all error handlers cause two distinct failure modes: bare `catch {}` silently swallows real bugs (missing files, API errors, permission issues), while `catch (err) { log(err) }` produces noise when expected/sentinel errors fire on every poll cycle — both bury real failures.
**Fix**: Always catch specific, expected errors first and suppress or downgrade them; let everything else propagate or log at error level:
  try { ... }
  catch (err) {
    if (err instanceof UnsupportedOperationError) return  // expected no-op
    if (err instanceof ENOENT) return                     // handled elsewhere
    logger.error('unexpected error', err)                 // real failures only
  }

